National Automotive Design and Development Council (NADDC) have designed a mobile ambulance for communities that are difficult to reach due to bad roads in the country. The Director General of the agency, Jelani Aliyu disclosed this in an interview with newsmen in Sokoto. According to him, the vehicle if manufactured would save lives of rural dwellers as it would contain all the necessary lifesaving equipment. He explained that the ambulance was designed to cope in difficult terrain within the country. Aliyu also said that the agency had designed other luxury vehicles that would suit Nigerian environment. “We will give the designs to private sector for mass production,” he said.  Nigeria to adopt global fuel economy initiative - Automobile Council Electric cars: Pilot production programme takes off soon - FG Senate commends NADDC over made in Nigeria vehicles initiative